American Water Works Company, Inc. provides water and wastewater services to customers in the US and Canada.
 As of December 31, 2008, it has provided drinking water, waste water, and other water-related services for approximately 15 million people in 32… MoreAmerican Water Works Company, Inc. provides water and wastewater services to customers in the US and Canada.
 As of December 31, 2008, it has provided drinking water, waste water, and other water-related services for approximately 15 million people in 32 states and in Ontario, Canada. American Water Works Company, Inc. was spun off from RWE Aktiengesellschaft in 2008.
American Water Works Company, Inc. provides water and wastewater services to customers in the US and Canada.
 As of December 31, 2008, it has provided drinking water, waste water, and other water-related services for approximately 15 million people in 32… MoreAmerican Water Works Company, Inc. provides water and wastewater services to customers in the US and Canada.
 As of December 31, 2008, it has provided drinking water, waste water, and other water-related services for approximately 15 million people in 32 states and in Ontario, Canada. American Water Works Company, Inc. was spun off from RWE Aktiengesellschaft in 2008.

IT Structure
•The IT department at the American Water Works Company, Inc. leads internal technical initiatives from the company's headquarters in Voorhees, NJ.
•The data center is located in Hershey, PA.
•At the various locations, managers oversee IT support areas, such as the Missouri-American Water plant.
•However, the top IT executives at headquarters provide centralized decision making for the IT operations of the company's various plants and offices in North America.

